The President's Weekly Address highlights the steps taken by the administration to remove wasteful regulations and boost employment. Two pieces of legislation were signed to eliminate burdens on the economy, including an anti-coal regulation and a costly regulation imposed on American energy companies. The President also emphasized the importance of empowering women in the economy, hosting a roundtable with women business leaders and announcing the creation of a joint US-Canada council for women entrepreneurs. Additionally, the President reaffirmed the strong bond with Israel and the commitment to combat terrorism. The address concludes with a reminder that the administration is dedicated to working for the American people.